# Main Program

## Purpose

The Main Program is responsible for system initialization and coordination of all software modules.

It does not process MIDI messages, control the keyboard or communicate directly with the shift registers.

---

## Description

The Main Program creates all software module objects, performs their initialization and controls the execution sequence of the firmware.

During the main program loop, it receives MIDI messages, updates the keyboard state and transfers the updated buffer to the shift register chain.

---

## Public Interface

The Main Program uses the standard Arduino functions:

* `setup()`;
* `loop()`.

All other functionality is implemented in separate software modules.

---

## Operating Principle

After startup, the `setup()` function initializes all software modules.

The `loop()` function continuously performs:

* MIDI message reception;
* keyboard state update;
* transmission of the updated keyboard buffer to the 74HC595 shift register chain.

The Main Program therefore coordinates the operation of the entire firmware.

---

## Limitations

Version 1.0 uses sequential event processing.

All modules operate within a single main loop without multitasking or interrupt-driven processing.

